original: Johansson, Gunnar Emanuel, prakt, läkare, Göteborg, f. 27/9/99 i Abo, Finl., av grosshandl. Emanuel J. o. Anna Österberg. G. 35 m. Elin Maria Nykvist. Barn: Gunlög f. 36, Barbro 40, Ulla 44. — Stud:ex. i Abo 20, med. kand. i Sthlm 27 o. med. lic. där 34. Tf. prov:läk. i Skönneruds, Orsa, Grönskåra, Högsäters o. Mjölby distr. kort. tider 34 o. 35, prakt. läk. i Gbg sed. 35 o. i Mölndal 35-42:
translated: Johansson, Gunnar Emanuel, physician, Gothenburg, born September 27th, 1899 in Abo, Finland, son of merchant Emanuel J. and Anna Österberg. He married Elin Maria Nykvist in 1935 and has three children: Gunlög (born 1936), Barbro (born 1940), and Ulla (born 1944). He passed his student examination in Abo in 1920, obtained his medical degree in Stockholm in 1927, and became a licensed physician there in 1934. He worked as a temporary probationary physician in Skönneruds, Orsa, Grönskåra, Högsäters, and Mjölby districts for brief periods in 1934 and 1935. He has been a practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1935 and in Mölndal from 1935 to 1942.
